# Blade Components Usage

**When**: Implementing UI components in Blade templates for the application.

**Then**:
- ALWAYS prioritize native Filament Blade components for UI elements.
- Use `<x-filament::...>` syntax for Filament components.
- Avoid custom Blade components unless absolutely necessary.

**Because**:
- Ensures consistency in UI/UX across the application.
- Leverages Filament's built-in accessibility features.
- Simplifies maintenance by using standardized components.

**Examples**:

*Correct*:
```blade
<x-filament::button>
    Submit
</x-filament::button>
```

*Incorrect*:
```blade
<x-custom-button>
    Submit
</x-custom-button>
```

**See**:
- [Filament Blade Components](https://filamentphp.com/docs/3.x/support/blade-components/overview)
